    <div class="clear-block clear">&nbsp;</div>
  
  <div class="content"><p>The media appears to be gorging on the 2% drop today in Gold and 11% drop in the last 4 months. Gold's demise today appears triggered by JPY's dump at around 8amET - though longer-term, it appears gold and stocks are recoupling in the reflation trade from around the start of QE2. At $1600, gold is back at August 2012 levels but +134% from the 2008 Lehman 'event'.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2013/02/20130215_goldspx2.jpg"><img src="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2013/02/20130215_goldspx2_0.jpg" width="600" height="324" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2013/02/20130215_goldspx1.jpg"><img src="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2013/02/20130215_goldspx1_0.jpg" width="600" height="323" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>Charts: Bloomberg</em></p>


